The paper deals with decision making under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of probability measures and imprecise probability models also suggests a connection to computational statistics (cs.CE) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper introduces a mathematical framework for decision making, which could be of interest to researchers in game theory (cs.GT).
